                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13593971" author="jcoveney" created="Tue, 5 Mar 2013 22:02:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is probably a good thing (despite the extreme verbosity of DEBUG...and perhaps because of it).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13593990" author="julienledem" created="Tue, 5 Mar 2013 22:15:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What would be useful is to have a log4j.properties for tests in a known location that is automatically picked up in test and can be easily modified on a case by case basis.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13594005" author="cheolsoo" created="Tue, 5 Mar 2013 22:28:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is what I have.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;I added a log4j.properties under conf.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;I set systemenv to point to it in build.xml.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Does this make sense?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13604076" author="daijy" created="Sat, 16 Mar 2013 01:29:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Make sense, but would like set the default to warning. Don&apos;t need too much logs in most cases.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13604122" author="cheolsoo" created="Sat, 16 Mar 2013 05:24:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure. I lowered the logging level to INFO, which is the current default value.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13604127" author="daijy" created="Sat, 16 Mar 2013 05:48:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13604128" author="cheolsoo" created="Sat, 16 Mar 2013 05:56:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you Daniel for the review. I committed to trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
